import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zipcodes_per_state = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    plt.bar(zipcodes_per_state['state'], zipcodes_per_state['zip_code'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across states?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    county_zip = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    county_zip = county_zip.sort_values(by='zip_code', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(county_zip['county'], county_zip['zip_code'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across counties?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(state_counts, labels=state_counts.index)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of states in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    county_zip = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    county_zip.columns = ['county', 'zip_count']
    county_zip = county_zip.sort_values('zip_count', ascending=False)
    county_zip = county_zip.reset_index(drop=True)
    county_zip['percentage'] = county_zip['zip_count']/county_zip['zip_count'].sum()*100
    county_zip['label'] = county_zip['county'] + ' (' + county_zip['percentage'].apply(lambda x: '{:.2f}%'.format(x)) + ')'
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.pie(county_zip['zip_count'], labels=county_zip['label'], startangle=90, counterclock=False, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of counties in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
